ml_tags: “To the world you may just be a teacher, but to your students, you were the world.” A heart of gold stopped beating / Working hands at rest / God broke our hearts to prove to us / He only takes the best / Leaves and flowers may wither / The golden sun may set / But the hearts that loved you dearly / Are the ones that won’t forget. A loving son, brother, father, uncle & grandfather, tender and kind, what a beautiful memory you left behind. Jotham Dzinopana MWENEZIKO 12/07/1943 SUNSET 23/01/2003 THE HEADMASTER CHOMUGOMO "Muchavovora" VaCHADHLAMUKONDE Sleep well KUSVUTA.
